      "side": 1,
      "message": "Thinking about it some more, I don\u0027t see a problem with the rounding up to kMinHeapAllocCount (that\u0027s free real estate) but the 50% growth factor is definitely not the caller\u0027s intent.\n\nJust now, I\u0027ve half-put-together a CL that turns off the 50% growth factor if you\u0027re constructing or reserve_back\u0027ing, but leaves it on for mutating operations like push_back/pop_back/etc. It\u0027s just an extra arg:\n\n    void checkRealloc(int delta, bool addExtraSpace \u003d true) {\n\nIt leaves the kMinHeapAllocCount rounding-up alone since that\u0027s zero cost.\n\nWhat do you think about this idea? I expect that between this CL and my described change, we\u0027d have everything sorted out.",
